|||In a pot of salted boiling water, cook pasta until al dente, rinse under cold water and drain.
|||Place eggs in a saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring water to a boil; 
cover, remove from heat, and let eggs stand in hot water for 10 to 12 minutes. 
Remove from hot water, cool, peel and chop.
|||In a large bowl, combine the pasta, eggs, pickles, celery and green onions. Pour dressing over salad and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper to taste; 
serve chilled.
